Now this is the icing on the cake, so to speak.  Those sanctions were authorized by the U.N.  Here's the exact words of the U.N. in resolution 1441.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>1. Decides that Iraq has been and remains in material breach of its obligations under relevant resolutions, including resolution 687 (1991), in particular through Iraq's failure to cooperate with United Nations inspectors and the IAEA, and to complete the actions required under paragraphs 8 to 13 of resolution 687 (1991);<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The United Nations itself says that Iraq is in material breach of its obligations.  Not me, not you, not President Bush, the U.N.<br>
<br>
So basically, this guy is anti-U.N. because he condemned the actions of the U.N. but since he is the king of spin he says this...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I do know that the only leader threatening the world with nuclear weapons and pre-emptive attack is George W. Bush.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
So. Patootie, I kept an open mind.  I read the whole first link, but gave up on the second one because link after link is just like Charlie.<br>
<br>
So I throw it back at you.  Keep an open mind.  Go back and read all the U.N. resolutions.  All of them.  Then tell me who has an open mind unless of course you don't believe in the U.N. any more than Charlie does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/btherathetravelagency.showUserPublicProfile?gid=joekreeper1>joekreeper1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Toade, remember them?</span><br>  Posts: 268<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(3/25/03 6:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm68.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=84>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Promise to the Anti-War Advocates</span><hr size=1> Ive seen lots of right wingers ( myself included ) but the only one to post a racial slur was Jur, ( he was quoting , I think The movie Three Kings  NOT calling Arabs sand niggers)<br>
